      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BUFFALO COWBOY (1) is a talented type and proved too strong last time to win by 3.5 lengths at this track in a handy 19.89 beating Best Dressed. Winner at his latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Can measure up again. UBIQUITOUS (2) comes off an average run last start when eighth at Sale over 435m behind Lindenow Buster (25.12) in a Grade 4/5. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings three times from five starts. Warrants plenty of respect. PAW SAPPHIRE (8) turned in a better effort at Sandown last start, finishing second behind Jorogumo (29.76) in a Grade 5. Led around the bend before fighting on well and should give a sight. Was a winner at her only start from this draw. Winning chance. HE'S A COLLINDA (4) is hard to fault of late and is a strong top-three hope again.",
